    • Enum Constant Detail

      • EMPTY

        public static final ResultStatus EMPTY
        There were no requirements to check.

        This can be the case if all requirements target a different target type or are filtered out. The EMPTY result is equivalent to a SUCCESS and will return true in Result.success().

      • CANCELLED

        public static final ResultStatus CANCELLED
        The check or execution was cancelled.

        This most likely happened thru an event that was cancelled by a user. Cancelled results will be considered a FAILURE but only if all results are cancelled.

      • SUCCESS

        public static final ResultStatus SUCCESS
        The requirement(s) were all successfully checked. This will only be the case if all underlying requirements AND target checks are successful.

      • FAILURE

        public static final ResultStatus FAILURE
        One of the requirements was not successfully checked.

        As soon as anyone of the underlying requirement checks fails, the whole result fails.

      • ERROR

        public static final ResultStatus ERROR
        Any of the requirement checks had an error.

        When any of the checks for any requirement and any target errors the whole result will be in an error state.
